						               													<description>Designed to recreate actual battles, In Deo Veritas focuses on the command decisions needed to maintain the motivation of the army. The six actual battle scenarios provide a range of different challenges from the warfare of the seventeenth century.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Battles are played at the brigade level with all major elements are on 75mm/3&amp;quot; wide bases. &amp;#10;Using smaller scale figures (6-15mm) lets players give their units a realistic feel. &amp;#10;The ground scale of 1&amp;quot; = 40yds means the typical 6ft x 4 ft table is large enough to accommodate most battles of the period.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Most players will already have everything needed to play (d6, tape measure and a deck of cards).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To learn the rules will take 2 hours or so using some of the smaller battles. Once you have become familiar with the core elements then your games will flow more quickly and a larger battle such as Wittstock should last for 3-4 hours depending on the arrival of the reinforcements!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Nothing is certain; but generals that hone their skills are more likely to be victorious.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
